external_knowledge:
- 'Cumulative average rating' refers to the running total of average ratings for games on each platform, ordered by the average rating in descending order and the game title in ascending order;
- 'Total languages supported' indicates the number of languages a game supports, which can affect its accessibility and popularity;
- 'Platform' refers to the specific gaming platform where the game is available, such as Android, PlayStation 3, etc.

- "Top 10 platforms" refers to the platforms with the highest average ratings;
- "Cultivated the highest average ratings" means the platforms have games with the highest average ratings;
- "Sunflowers reaching for the sky" is a metaphor for platforms with high ratings.

- "Average user engagement" can include metrics such as play time, number of installs, and number of active users;
- "Number of languages supported" refers to the count of different languages a game is available in;
- "User base for those languages" refers to the total number of users who speak the languages supported by the game.

sql:
SELECT platform_name
FROM platforms
ORDER BY market_share DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "Largest communities" refers to languages with the highest number of users;
- "Available games" refers to the total count of distinct games supporting each language;
- "Average ratings" are calculated per game and platform combination.

- "blossomed into vibrant gardens" refers to platforms with a thriving and active community;
- "at least five games" indicates that the platform must have a minimum of five games available;
- "bustling" refers to the number of active users, with more active users meaning a more active platform.

- "sprouted their digital seeds" refers to games being released on platforms;
- "dawn of the new millennium" refers to January 1, 2000;
- "close of the decade" refers to December 31, 2009;
- "fertile ground to grow" means the game was released on a platform (`gp.release_date IS NOT NULL`).

- "Most beloved and widely recognized platforms" refers to platforms with a market share greater than 10%;
- "Most cherished game" refers to a game with a popularity score greater than 90;
- "More than 1000 users who have rated it" indicates a game with more than 1000 user ratings;
- "High-quality translation" refers to a game with a translation quality of 'high';
- "Shining brightly among the waves" implies the game is the top result when sorted by popularity in descending order.

- "Versatile" refers to games released on multiple platforms;
- "Strongest soil" refers to the platform with the highest market share for each game;
- "Average popularity" is the mean popularity score of a game across all platforms.

- 'strong presence' refers to games with a popularity score greater than 50;
- 'well-received' refers to platforms with an average popularity score greater than 60;
- 'peak of the average popularity wave' refers to the maximum value of the average popularity.
